In article <wfdBF0m00iV3I4seZk@andrew.cmu.edu> David Reeve Sward <sward+@CMU.EDU> writes:
>Does PGP's LZW(?) compression of files before encryption also add known
>plaintext?

I don't know what PGP does, but the header of a compressed output can be
pre-encrypted by XOR with a one-time key -- and that key piece can be part
of the per-message key which is passed along under RSA.

